        <p>You can do a whole bunch of other stuff with animate.css when you combine it with jQuery or add your own CSS rules. Dynamically add animations using jQuery with ease:</p>
        <pre><code data-fc-modules="code">$('#yourElement').addClass('animated bounceOutLeft');</code></pre>
        <p>You can also detect when an animation ends:</p>
        <pre><code data-fc-modules="code">$('#yourElement').one('webkitAnimationEnd mozAnimationEnd MSAnimationEnd oanimationend animationend', doSomething);</code></pre>
        <p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CBQGl6zokMs" target="_blank">View a video tutorial</a> on how to use Animate.css with jQuery here. </p>
